This documentation describes the Evolven Change Analytics for Pivotal Platform. The 
Evolven Change Analytics agent for Pivotal Platform collects inventory and configuration of the Pivotal Platform platform and
applications running on this platform. It also detects and reports changes in the collected configuration. 


## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

The Evolven Change Analytics agent for Pivotal Platform includes a configuration collector that connects to Pivotal Platform and 
regularly scans the platform and applications running on it. The agent reports collected data and 
detected changes to a central Evolven Change Analytics Server that consolidates, cleans, correlates, and analyzes all 
the collected information. 

Users can access the Evolven Change Analytics Server to interactively review detected changes and differences, their 
risks, impact, and correlation to investigated issues. In addition to interactive analysis the users can set up 
alerts, reports, and other types of notifications to be generated by the Evolven Change Analytics Server. The 
reports are sent when a risky change or drift is detected in a particular Pivotal Platform environment or 
across multiple environments.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

Evolven Change Analytics for Pivotal Platform includes the following key features:

* Granular collection of inventory and configuration of applications running on Pivotal Platform
* Granular collection of inventory and configuration of the Pivotal Platform platform
* Detection of actual changes and drift in the configuration of applications and Pivotal Platform

